            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">31.103</ph> Contracts with commercial organizations.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <p id="d1924e13" class="- topic/p ">This category includes all contracts and contract modifications for supplies, services, or experimental, developmental, or research work negotiated with organizations other than educational institutions (see <ph class="- topic/ph ">
					          <xref href="FAR-i1086129.dita#i1086129"
                     base="i1086129"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">31.104</xref>
				        </ph>), construction and architect-engineer contracts (see <ph class="- topic/ph ">
					          <xref href="FAR-i1086146.dita#i1086146"
                     base="i1086146"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">31.105</xref>
				        </ph>), State and local governments (see <ph class="- topic/ph ">
					          <xref href="FAR-i1086200.dita#i1086200"
                     base="i1086200"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">31.107</xref>
				        </ph>) and nonprofit organizations (see <ph class="- topic/ph ">
					          <xref href="FAR-i1086212.dita#i1086212"
                     base="i1086212"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">31.108</xref>
				        </ph>) on the basis of cost.</p>
			      <ol id="d1910e40" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1924e44" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The cost principles and procedures in <xref href="FAR-i1084539.dita#i1084539"
                        base="i1084539"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpart  31.2</xref> and agency supplements shall be used in pricing negotiated supply, service, experimental, developmental, and research contracts and contract modifications with commercial organizations whenever cost analysis is performed as required by <xref href="FAR-i1106135.dita#i1106135"
                        base="i1106135"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">15.404-1</xref>(c).</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1924e59" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            In addition, the contracting officer shall incorporate the cost principles and procedures in <xref href="FAR-i1084539.dita#i1084539"
                        base="i1084539"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpart  31.2</xref> and agency supplements by reference in contracts with commercial organizations as the basis for-</p>
					          <ol id="d1910e68" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1924e72" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Determining reimbursable costs under-</p>
							              <ol id="d1910e78" class="- topic/ol ">
								                <li class="- topic/li ">
									                  <p id="d1924e82" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
										                    Cost-reimbursement contracts and cost-reimbursement subcontracts under these contracts performed by commercial organizations and</p>
								                </li>
								                <li class="- topic/li ">
									                  <p id="d1924e91" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
										                    The cost-reimbursement portion of time-and-materials contracts except when material is priced on a basis other than at cost (see <xref href="FAR-i1103674.dita#i1103674"
                                    base="i1103674"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">16.601</xref>(c)(3));</p>
								                </li>
							              </ol>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1924e105" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Negotiating indirect cost rates (see <xref href="FAR-i1075062.dita#i1075062"
                              base="i1075062"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  42.7</xref>);</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1924e117" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Proposing, negotiating, or determining costs under terminated contracts (see <xref href="FAR-i1068616.dita#i1068616"
                              base="i1068616"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">49.103</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1069003.dita#i1069003"
                              base="i1069003"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">49.113</xref>);</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1924e132" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Price revision of fixed-price incentive contracts (see <xref href="FAR-i1104985.dita#i1104985"
                              base="i1104985"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">16.204</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1104478.dita#i1104478"
                              base="i1104478"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">16.403</xref>);</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1924e147" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Price redetermination of price redetermination contracts (see <xref href="FAR-i1104997.dita#i1104997"
                              base="i1104997"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">16.205</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1105032.dita#i1105032"
                              base="i1105032"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">16.206</xref>); and</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1924e163" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(6)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Pricing changes and other contract modifications.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
